### Phase 3.5: Initial Batch Indexing (One-Time Job)

**Critical Step:** Your MinIO bucket has **300,000+ existing images**. The webhook system only processes *new* uploads. You must run the batch indexer once to ingest the backlog.

#### 3.5.1 Run Batch Indexer Container

This runs as a detached process inside the Docker network, allowing it to talk to MinIO (`http://host.docker.internal:9000` or production URL) and Postgres/Redis directly.

**Command to start indexing:**

```bash
# Run the batch indexer script inside the 'app' container
# Using 'run --rm' creates a temporary container that cleans up after itself
# We mount the volume to ensure logs are persisted if needed

dmpy_command="python tools/batch_indexer.py"

# If you want to force re-index everything (overwrite existing embeddings):
# dmpy_command="python tools/batch_indexer.py --force"

docker-compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml run --rm app $dmpy_command
```

#### 3.5.2 Monitor Progress

The indexer prints progress to the console. If you ran it in detached mode (`-d`), view logs:

```bash
# If you ran with -d, check logs:
docker logs -f <container_id>
```

**Performance Estimates (for 300,000 images):**

| Hardware | Speed | Estimated Time |
|----------|-------|----------------|
| **GPU (CUDA)** | ~2-4 images/sec | **21 - 42 hours** |
| **CPU Only** | ~0.5-1 image/sec | **3.5 - 7 days** |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Ensure **no other heavy workloads** are running if using CPU.
> - The indexer automatically handles **thumbnails** creation.
> - It skips already-indexed files unless `--force` is used.
> - You can stop and resume at any time (it checks [get_existing_keys](file:///c:/Users/ACHAL.TRIVEDI/Downloads/InHouse-Indexed%20Search/tools/batch_indexer.py#25-34) on startup).

